This paper deals with the problem of motion planning for robot manipulators, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The paper also involves the use of computer vision techniques for object detection and recognition, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel method that integrates online learning techniques for grasp selection, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of obstacle avoidance, which is a key issue in control systems (cs.SY).
